posts.subject: whitepill thread
posts.body:
Every place one turns one finds coordinated efforts to trim /pol/ ideas in their bud, to mock them and give the opinion that other like-minded people are far between, at odds with the vast majority and doomed to fail.

It is well documented that leftist ideas are overrepresented in all public discourse and information sharing and thus in reality the world is not as bad ('left') as msm/social media/politics make it seem.
But this knowledge itself is often not enough. Take the constant exposure to said world-views and add to this the incessant redpills and an anon might begin to lose his hope and willingness to further his cause.

It is important to realise that these feelings, this  demoralisation, is not natural but rather a product of intentional and constant psychological warfare fought against you by them "for the sake of social stability". This must be realised and then must be equally intentionally and ruthlessly countered.

Thus, whitepills.
Please provide some, to imbue the faltering anon with healthy optimism and rekindle his will to continue the struggle.
I'll start


my first thread, pls no bully.

posts.subject: please help solve issues
posts.body:
I'm running arch and 08chan is usable, but I have issues. Attached are pngs of relevant zeronet log snippets as well as whole debug.log of last session.
Insights would be greatly appreciated.

	i) memoryleak as shown by debug_systemctl_status.png. It grows until zeronet is stopped. Seeing this I've gone to inspect debug.log for info on findHashIds error.



	ii) debug_greenlet.png shows lines >= 9379 of debug.log and shows new worker being added, and his hashtable not being asked, then workers drop to zero followed by an error in findHashIds. A few lines later the same error is repeated without a new worker being added in between, which confuses me.



	iii) also in debug_greenlet.png there is verification error (debug.log line 9395):

WARNING  Site:1DdPHe..Vi9D data/users/14wXfkR1LreXoF9EQz7oqAwXGxbeFEMSeg/content.json: verify sign error: VerifyError: Include too large 892B > 0B in ContentManager.py line 960 > ContentManager.py line 853 > ContentManager.py line 869

despite folder data/users/14w.. not even existing. The same error is repeated many times with many different (non-existent) usernames.



	iv) unexplained 'tasks started' jumps:
log shows tasks started: 1 (line 316), next is tasks started: 9134 (line 488) as shown in debug_tasks_started.png.
In between is a very long line Bad files: {u'data/users/1MCQ....} with a bunch of u'data/users/<username>/.. as shown in debug_bad_files.png.
The first of which (1MCQ..) is the same one for which a new task is created on line 488 but which doesnt exist in my /data/users folder. Some other usernames among Bad files, however, do exist.



	v) more of an oddity than an issue:
log shows worker 193.11.134.38:11545 getting added twice (lines 8518, 8814) without getting closed in between, is this wrong?



If you have any ideas, please, let me know. Thanks.

EDIT: Can't upload log/txt/md so here is link to debug.log:

https://anonfile.com/iamaDd32ne/debug_log

If you're afraid to download this, tell me how to upload it differently.

>>99d17cd6-eb9d-4247-bdf4-18e2cff47cad
Of course. Do you need any help setting it up?

torfag or not, don't click 'Download and help distribute all files' because the way millchan is written, it would request  all the tens of thousands of files simultaneously, eating through your memory. Also connection with UIServer and trackers would be lost due to the unusual traffic you're generating (they would assume you're malicious).

Instead, pin boards one at a time, but note this might still eat up huge amounts of memory.
